  "name": "Wan 2.2 Bernini-R — image editing with a reference image",
  "description": "Edit an image guided by a second reference image. Upload the image to edit, a reference image (a look, subject, or object to bring in), and a text instruction — the Bernini-R model (Wan 2.2) regenerates the image following the prompt and the reference while keeping the composition.\n\n• **Edit type**: \"Image Editing\" edits the first image guided by the reference; \"Subject to Image\" brings the reference subject into the scene.\n• **Fast mode** (Turbo LoRA) is on by default — ~6 steps. Turn it off for slower, higher-quality 40-step runs.\n\nFor editing by text alone (no reference image), use the plain image-editing version instead.",
